It looks like we may not need transactions for classes generated, but since dynamic coverage includes those transaction classes, focusing on Ehcache core transactions is necessary. I'll mention relevant research facts, like how the POM indicates JTA is provided and that Bitronix manages global transactions. I need to clarify the agent guidance around skipping update checks and configuring properties for Bitronix. I should also finalize whether to include `org.codehaus.btm:btm:2.1.4` versus the POM's version of 2.0.1.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Ehcache-core 2.5.0 can be used in-memory without services, but meaningful coverage of its transaction/XA path needs JTA and a transaction manager; the existing 2.4.4 tests already require these, and Ehcache documentation describes global transactions as JTA-controlled with Bitronix as a common standalone manager.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.transaction:jta:1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"ehcache-core declares JTA as a provided dependency and transaction/XA classes such as CacheTransactionHelper and DefaultTransactionManagerLookup expose javax.transaction APIs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.btm:btm:2.1.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix is a documented standalone JTA transaction manager for Ehcache global transaction tests, and the existing coverage uses it to exercise DefaultTransactionManagerLookup.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix marks the JMS API as optional but its resource classes reference it; adding the spec avoids optional-classpath gaps during test and native-image analysis.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set `net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck=true` in tests, or use `Configuration.updateCheck(false)`, to avoid Ehcache's background update checker. If exercising Bitronix, create an isolated temporary `bitronix.properties`, set `bitronix.tm.configuration` for the test, disable JMX, use a null journal, clear the property afterward, and shut down the transaction manager and all CacheManager instances.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Ehcache 2.5.0 adds the SizeOf engine and embedded sizeof-agent code; native-image failures there are likely metadata/runtime-initialization issues rather than a missing external dependency.\",\n    \"Old Bitronix and Ehcache APIs can start background services; tests should keep configuration isolated and always shut resources down.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f2422469f35fb67016a42905740f88197a244350eda9feec4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1236, "output": 1133, "cacheRead": 55296, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57665, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782747211754, "responseId": "resp_0f2422469f35fb67016a42904c55e4819785def5ae417405b6"}, "toolResults": []}
